1
00:00:05,858 --> 00:00:07,321
We think, you know

2
00:00:07,321 --> 00:00:11,918
“I have five hundred friends
on Facebook.”

3
00:00:11,924 --> 00:00:16,405
You have five trillion friends
in the spiritual world

4
00:00:16,462 --> 00:00:19,870
[Five Trillion Friends]

5
00:00:20,408 --> 00:00:24,480
who are trying to help us.

6
00:00:24,542 --> 00:00:27,635
They’re trying to friend us,

7
00:00:27,713 --> 00:00:33,560
and we’re riveted to the persons, 
places, things of this world.

8
00:00:35,891 --> 00:00:38,866
Sudurlabhā bhāgavatā hi loke
[Hbs: 13.2]—

9
00:00:38,867 --> 00:00:45,224
а real devotee in this world is rare,
very rare to find,

10
00:00:45,224 --> 00:00:48,338
but Guru Mahārāj said, 
“In this world.

11
00:00:48,338 --> 00:00:53,605
But there’s another world
where everyone is a pure devotee”,

12
00:00:54,424 --> 00:00:56,385
and that’s the greater world.

13
00:00:56,385 --> 00:01:01,738
If you compare the two worlds,
from spiritual analysis,

14
00:01:01,738 --> 00:01:05,177
that world is vast.

15
00:01:06,178 --> 00:01:12,739
This world
has been referred to variously—

16
00:01:12,739 --> 00:01:17,591
as a clouded portion 
of the spiritual sky.

17
00:01:17,623 --> 00:01:22,160
When Goloka Vṛndāvan 
is discussed

18
00:01:22,160 --> 00:01:26,691
as being sixteen krośas
or thirty-two square miles, mystically.

19
00:01:26,691 --> 00:01:31,045
We’re told:
“Well, that sounds, like, small.”

20
00:01:31,092 --> 00:01:36,165
We say, “Yes”, and within an atom
of the dust there,

21
00:01:36,165 --> 00:01:40,605
are innumerable Vaikuṇṭha planets.

22
00:01:42,894 --> 00:01:46,477
It means we’re going to have
to re-adjust ourselves

23
00:01:46,477 --> 00:01:48,283
to properly conceive
these things.

24
00:01:48,283 --> 00:01:54,086
It can only be conceived of 
through grace,

25
00:01:54,087 --> 00:01:56,486
as the sun’s illumination.

26
00:01:56,486 --> 00:01:59,716
The sun allows
the eye to see.

27
00:01:59,716 --> 00:02:00,682
What did Guru Mahārāj say?

28
00:02:00,682 --> 00:02:04,863
“Faith is the halo of Rādhārāṇī.”

29
00:02:04,863 --> 00:02:07,336
She’s revealing Kṛṣṇa,

30
00:02:07,351 --> 00:02:11,704
but out of service necessity,
not out of curiosity.

31
00:02:11,704 --> 00:02:15,630
If someone has a genuine
service necessity,

32
00:02:15,630 --> 00:02:18,967
they will journey
to the centre of the infinite,

33
00:02:18,967 --> 00:02:24,474
they’ll be fully endowed
beyond their wildest dreams

34
00:02:24,474 --> 00:02:29,270
with serving capacity—
if that’s what it really is.

